-> Laravel used blade template engine
-> extension : .blade.php stored in resources/views directory
-> returned using global helper method view()
-> Displaying Data:
    - by wrapping the variable in curly braces {{variable_name}}
    Note : {{}} echo statements are automatically sent through PHP's htmlspecialchars function to prevent XSS(Cross-site scripting) attack.
-> HTML Entity Encoding: 
    - boot() method in AppServiceProvider
    - Blade::withoutDoubleEncoding()
    - Displaying Unescaped Data : {!! $variable !!}
-> Blade & JavaScript Frameworks
    - @ symbol
    - Rendering JSON : 
        - var app = <?php echo json_encode($array); ?>;
        - Illuminate\Support\Js::from($array) (instanceof upper method)
        -  JS::from($array)
    - The @verbatim Directive : you do not have to prefix each Blade echo statement with an @ symbol
-> Blade Directives:
    - If Statements : @if,@elseif,@else,@endif
    - @unless ... @endunless
    - @isset(is defined and is not null...) and @empty(is empty)
    - Authentication directives : @auth and @guest
    - Environment Directives : @production OR @env([environment list])
    - Section Directives : @hassection...@endif AND @@sectionMissing...@endif